original: Högquist, Ernst Sigurd, kyrkoherde. Asbysand, f. 6/1/05 i Högsby, Kalmar 1., av Viktor H. o. Anna Jo’hansson. G. 40 m. Inga-Greta Norell. Barn: Christina f. 41, Anders 43, Elisabet 45. — Stud :ex. i Sthlm 25, teol. fil. ex. 27, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 31. Past:adj. i Ekeby, tf. kyrkoh. i Asby 32, kyr-koh. i Asby o. Torpa past. sed. 39. Ordf. i kyrkostämma, past :kyrkostäm-ma, folksk:styr. o. Ydre-krets. av Sv-RK.
translated: Högquist, Ernst Sigurd, pastor. Born on January 6th 1905 in Högsby, Kalmar county, son of Viktor H. and Anna Johansson. Married to Inga-Greta Norell in 1940 with whom he has three children: Christina (born in 1941), Anders (born in 1943), and Elisabet (born in 1945). He graduated from Stockholm University with a bachelor's degree in theology in 1925, followed by a degree in theological philosophy in 1927, and a degree in practical theology, as well as ordainment as a pastor in Linköping in 1931. He worked as a pastor's assistant in Ekeby, temporary pastor in Asby in 1932, and as a pastor in Asby and Torpa pastorate from 1939. He served as chairman of the church meeting, the pastor's church meeting, the local school board, and the Ydre district of the Swedish Red Cross.
